The '''Baja Beach Club''' was an exclusive [[nightclub]] in [[Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]], [[Spain]].

The club made worldwide news in 2004, when it began offering to implant [[VeriChip]]s into its [[VIP]] customers for identification purposes.[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HTs48E0NFXI][http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/technology/3697940.stm] The club was criticised for making the implanted chips difficult to remove.<ref>[http://edition.cnn.com/2004/TECH/10/05/spark.bajabeach/ CNN - The Price to pay for VIP status]</ref> The scheme has drawn strong criticism from civil liberty movements as well as religious organisations.{{Citation needed|date=September 2008}} 

At the location of the Baja Beach Club is now operates the Opium Mar Club, with a different concept.

