{{Politics of Gambia}}

The '''Gambian People's Party''' (GPP) was a [[political party]] in [[the Gambia]]. It was founded by [[Assan Musa Camara]] in February 1986 and formally launched on 29 March 1986. GPP was a splinter group of the governing [[People's Progressive Party (Gambia)|People's Progressive Party]]. The party got 15.5% of the votes in the [[Gambian general election, 1987|1987 parliamentary elections]] and 7.96% in the [[Gambian general election, 1992|1992 elections]], but it never won a parliamentary seat.<ref name="code">[http://www.codesria.org/Links/Publications/ad3_2000/edie.pdf Democracy in The Gambia by Carlene J Edie<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Camara contested as the presidential candidate of the party in 1987, and got 29,428 votes (14%). In the 1992 presidential election, he got 8% of the votes.<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/gm.html Elections in The Gambia<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

The party was banned after the 1994 military coup, and its leading members barred from participating in politics.<ref name="code"/>

