Each of the [[Lugbara people|Lugbara]] clans in [[Uganda]] has a distinct [[totem]] to represent it based on a characteristic living thing found in the clan's area. Nevertheless, the O'du ([[Leopard]]) is the general [[emblem]] representing all Lugbara and [[Arua]]. ==Symbols== {|Class=''wikitable'' |- !Clan !Totem |- |Aringa||''Ojuruko'' ([[Termite]]) |- |Ayivu||''Pala bi'' ([[Jute]]) |- |Koboko||''Yekeye'' (Red [[safari ant]]) |- |Madi ([[Adjumani]])||''Au'' ([[Rooster]]) |- |Madi Okollo||''Aswa'' ([[White ants]] in paste) |- |Maracha||''Kulu'' ([[Grasshopper]]) |- |Terego||''Odro'' ([[Rat]]) |- |Vurra||''Ago'' ([[Pumpkin]]) |}
