The '''Saddam Line''' consisted of defensive [[fortification]]s constructed by [[Saddam Hussein]]'s [[Iraqi Army]] on [[Kuwait]]'s border with [[Saudi Arabia]] after Iraq had [[Invasion of Kuwait|invaded and occupied Kuwait]] in August 1990.

The Western media presented fears that it would present a formidable obstacle to the [[Liberation of Kuwait campaign|liberation of Kuwait]], consisting of "flame trenches" (ditches filled with oil to be ignited in case of attack)<ref>{{cite web | author = Staff | date = n.d. | url=http://www.fas.org/irp/gulf/cia/960702/70086_01.htm |title=Iraq and the Gulf War 1990-1991 |publisher=([[CIA Directorate of Intelligence|Directorate of Intelligence]] document) [[United States Department of Defense|U.S. Department of Defense]] (via the [[Federation of American Scientists]]) |accessdate= February 24, 2012}}</ref><ref name=LATimes>{{cite news |title='Saddam Line' Falls Easily to Marines |author=[[Bob Drogin|Drogin, Bob]] | work =[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=February 25, 1991 |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1991-02-25/news/mn-1412_1_marine-division | accessdate = February 24, 2012}}</ref> and "sand berms, trench works, tank ditches, barbed wire and minefields",<ref>{{cite web | author = Staff | url=http://www.newsweek.com/1991/02/10/breaching-the-saddam-line.html |title=Breaching The 'Saddam Line' |work = [[Newsweek]] |date=February 10, 1991 |accessdate= February 24, 2012}}</ref> backed by the threat of chemical and biological weapons. However, those fears turned out to be unwarranted. The [[Coalition of the Gulf War|coalition]] assault, beginning at 4 a.m. on February 24, 1991, met "only sporadic resistance", and by 6:45&nbsp;a.m., troops had broken through the Saddam Line.<ref>{{cite book |chapterurl=http://gseis.ucla.edu/faculty/kellner/essays/gulfwarch8.pdf |title=The Persian Gulf TV War | format = [[Portable Document Format|PDF]]; [[Adobe Acrobat]] required | author = [[Douglas Kellner|Kellner, Douglas]] | year = 1992 | location = Boulder, Colorado | publisher= [[Westview Press]] (via the [[University of California, Los Angeles]]) | chapter = Chapter 8 – Countdown to the Ground War | accessdate= February 24, 2012 | isbn = 978-0-8133-1614-7}}</ref>

